wikipedia_page.main: William Henry Elliott (20 March 1925 – 21 January 2008), born in Bradford, was an English professional footballer and football manager. He played five times for the England national side.

response: Jensen played regularly through the 1973 season, and at age 30, he was expected to play for many years to come. * Billy Elliott (footballer) (1925–2008), English footballer and manager

*21 January 2008 – Billy Elliott, 82, former Sunderland winger who won five England caps. Also played for Bradford Park Avenue and Burnley, and later became manager of Darlington.
